<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="W" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Welsh" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Welsh,</orth> pertaining to Wales, or native of Wales: <bibl n="shak. wiv 2.1.209" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. II, 1, 209</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 3.1.100" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 100</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 5.3.13" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 3, 13</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 5.5.85" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 5, 85</bibl>. 145 <emph>(a W. goat).</emph> 172 <cit><quote>(W. flannel).</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 2.4.372" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A II, 4, 372</bibl></cit> (<emph>a W. hook,</emph> i. e. a sort of bill hooked at the end). <bibl n="shak. 1h4 3.1.247" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 247</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 4.7.112" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 IV, 7, 112</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 5.1.82" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 82</bibl>. <emph>the W.</emph> == the people of Wales: <bibl n="shak. 2h4 1.3.79" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B I, 3, 79</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 1.3.79" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B I, 3, 79</bibl> <emph>I am W.</emph> (== a Welshman) <bibl n="shak. h5 4.7.110" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 IV, 7, 110</bibl>; cf. <bibl n="shak. wiv 3.1.100" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. III, 1, 100</bibl>.<lb />Substantively, == the language of Wales: <bibl n="shak. 1h4 3.1.50" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A III, 1, 50</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 3.1.50" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A III, 1, 50</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 3.1.50" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A III, 1, 50</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 3.1.50" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A III, 1, 50</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 3.1.50" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A III, 1, 50</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 3.1.50" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A III, 1, 50</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 3.1.50" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A III, 1, 50</bibl>
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>